{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/manifests/43rd-annual-patterson-lecture-ricaurte-v-squez-morales-panama-canal-administrator.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"en":["43rd Annual Patterson Lecture: Ricaurte Vásquez Morales, Panama Canal Administrator"]},"homepage":[{"id":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes","type":"Text","label":{"en":["43rd Annual Patterson Lecture: Ricaurte Vásquez Morales, Panama Canal Administrator"]},"format":"text/html"}],"metadata":[{"label":{"en":["Description"]},"value":{"en":["Vasquez delivered the 43rd Annual William A. Patterson Transportation Lecture, held May 7, 2025, at the Walter Athletics Center Auditorium. Hosted by the Northwestern University Transportation Center (NUTC), the lecture is named for William A. “Pat” Patterson, a central figure in the US air transport industry for more than four decades who served as president and chairman of United Airlines from 1934 until his retirement in 1966. He was a life trustee of Northwestern University and was instrumental in the establishment and strategic leadership of the NUTC. \n\n"]}},{"label":{"en":["Language"]},"value":{"en":["English"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/43rd_annual_patterson_lecture_ricaurte_vásquez_morales_panama_canal_administrator/canvas/2","type":"Canvas","duration":5252,"annotations":[{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/manifests/43rd_annual_patterson_lecture_ricaurte_vásquez_morales_panama_canal_administrator-canvas2-1","type":"AnnotationPage","label":{"en":["Default"]},"items":[{"@context":"http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld","type":"Annotation","motivation":["commenting","tagging"],"id":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/43rd_annual_patterson_lecture_ricaurte_vásquez_morales_panama_canal_administrator/canvas/2/page1","body":[{"type":"TextualBody","value":"Panama Canal Administrator, Ricaurte Vasquez, shares climatological chronologies to establish a framework of environmental inevitability. By framing the water conflict purely around climate cycles and system \"reliability,\" the managerial discourse rationalizes hydraulic engineering as the only objective, apolitical response to nature.","format":"text/plain","motivation":"commenting"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"reservoir","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"dam","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"state mapping","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"}],"target":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/43rd_annual_patterson_lecture_ricaurte_vásquez_morales_panama_canal_administrator/canvas/2#t=3320,3370"},{"@context":"http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld","type":"Annotation","motivation":["commenting","tagging"],"id":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/43rd_annual_patterson_lecture_ricaurte_vásquez_morales_panama_canal_administrator/canvas/2/page1","body":[{"type":"TextualBody","value":"Vasquez implements a scalar shift that reframes infrastructure as a domestic public utility. By anchoring the project's legitimacy in the necessity of municipal water supply, the discourse establishes a moral hierarchy that complicates local claims to territorial sovereignty.","format":"text/plain","motivation":"commenting"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"reservoir","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"dam","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"state mapping","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"}],"target":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/43rd_annual_patterson_lecture_ricaurte_vásquez_morales_panama_canal_administrator/canvas/2#t=3371,3414"},{"@context":"http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld","type":"Annotation","motivation":["commenting","tagging"],"id":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/43rd_annual_patterson_lecture_ricaurte_vásquez_morales_panama_canal_administrator/canvas/2/page1","body":[{"type":"TextualBody","value":"ACP administrator explicitly acknowledges the structural friction of land flooding and social displacement. Rather than dismissing the threat, the narrative conceptualizes displacement as an administrative \"dilemma\" to be neutralized through communicative governance.","format":"text/plain","motivation":"commenting"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"reservoir","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"dam","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"state mapping","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"environmental legislation","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"}],"target":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/43rd_annual_patterson_lecture_ricaurte_vásquez_morales_panama_canal_administrator/canvas/2#t=3453,3466"},{"@context":"http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld","type":"Annotation","motivation":["commenting","tagging"],"id":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/43rd_annual_patterson_lecture_ricaurte_vásquez_morales_panama_canal_administrator/canvas/2/page1","body":[{"type":"TextualBody","value":"By substituting state social subsidies with corporate legal \"contracts,\" Vasquez addresses how political agency becomes individualized, conditioned to environmental stewardship. This framework reinforces the state's contemporary execution of the project, which was codified when RÃ­o Indio was integrated into the Panama Canal's watershed master plan for the 2026 fiscal cycle.","format":"text/plain","motivation":"commenting"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"reservoir","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"dam","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"state mapping","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"environmental legislation","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"}],"target":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/43rd_annual_patterson_lecture_ricaurte_vásquez_morales_panama_canal_administrator/canvas/2#t=3574,3590"}]}],"items":[{"id":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/43rd_annual_patterson_lecture_ricaurte_vásquez_morales_panama_canal_administrator-canvas2/paintings","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/43rd_annual_patterson_lecture_ricaurte_vásquez_morales_panama_canal_administrator-canvas2/paintings","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","body":{"id":"https://youtu.be/MmXL0LMcjCQ?si=bc9Kzoi3bmBOtar-","type":"Video","format":"unknown","duration":5252},"target":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/43rd_annual_patterson_lecture_ricaurte_vásquez_morales_panama_canal_administrator/canvas/2"}]}]}]}